  "description": "This dataset comprises functional near-infrared spectroscopy (fNIRS) measurements of hemodynamic brain responses to painful thermal and electrical stimuli during finger tapping tasks. The study investigates the specificity of cerebral hemodynamic responses to noxious stimulation, employing short separation regression techniques to improve statistical localization and account for autonomic response variability across different stimulus modalities.",
  "methods_description": "Data were collected using functional near-infrared spectroscopy (fNIRS) during tasks involving thermal and electrical stimulation combined with finger tapping. Short separation regression was applied to improve statistical significance and localization of hemodynamic responses.",
